\Pr(X=1\ \&\ Y=1)=pq
E(XY) = 0\cdot\Pr(XY=0) + 1\cdot\Pr(XY=1) = \Pr(XY=1)
XY=1
X=1
Y=1
0
\Pr(X=1\ \&\ Y=1)=pq
 X=\begin{cases} 1 & \text{with probability }p, \\ 0 & \text{with probability } 1-p, \end{cases} 
 Y=\begin{cases} 1 & \text{with probability }r, \\ 0 & \text{with probability } 1-r. \end{cases} 
 E(XY) - E(X)E(Y) = E(XY) - pq. 
